title: For Sale:  Browning Auto 5 12-gauge Shotgun  Made In The USA
postcontent: When WWII started, Browning went to Remington and asked them to produce a model 11 with the Browning logo stamped on it, since Belgium / FN was occupied by the Germans. Remington accepted the deal and made these during WWII.This is a Browning A5 12Ga Shotgun Early World War II The serial has a B before it and on the Barrel it is written "Browning Arms Company St. Louis MO" on the barrel.  This was an American made shotgun. These guns were true Auto-5s and included the Browning logo, but bore their own serial number range. The 12-ga models bore serial numbers beginning with a “B.”Condition = 90+ % the metal and walnut stock are in  great shape and cleanBarrel Length 28"The 2 Stars on the barrel indicated that the Choke is ModifiedBrowning Auto 5's have been produced for Browning in Belgium and later Japan. The brief relationship with Remington makes the WWII era A5 the only A5 produced in the US. As a result, this particular model is sometimes called the "American Browning."

title: For Sale:  1956 SKS Ghost gun 5 digit serial #
location: Dalto, Ringgold, FT O, Chattanooga, Cleveland, Dalton, Georgia
postcontent:
This is a true SKS Ghost gun with a 5 digit serial number and no Arsenal stamp. These carbines were manufactured shortly after the Russian government sold the plans, material and tooling for the SKS rifle to China.
 
The first manufactured carbines were called Soviet-Sino the serial number contained a Russian Cryllic as the first character of the serial number as well as a Tula star on the left of receiver in line with the serial number.
 
The Ghost was the next batch of carbines manufactured under direct Soviet supervision, before adopting the a Arsenal 26 triangle with the 3 Chinese characters denoting a type 56 military grade carbine in the later part of 1956. 
 
This as with all the Soviet-Sino, and Ghost guns have Soviet parts and Soviet QC/Proof stamps in several locations on the weapon and stock.
 
This SKS carbine is 100% matching including the stock. No cleaning kit or sling.
 
The bore is bright, with sharp rifling, the action is tight, trigger is crisp.
 
Excellent piece of history. Not exactly pretty, but very interesting a great shooter to add to your collection.
 
The SKS is a robust over built weapon for its caliber. Proven in combat in several conflicts, and will outlast most other carbines in its class.
 
A very big bang for the buck.
 
Thanks for looking.
Will trade for:
Pistols no .22's. Rifles must be interesting.
